---
description: Phaser test conventions
alwaysApply: false
globs: "**/*.{test,spec}.{ts,js}"
---

When writing or editing Phaser tests:

1. Name tests after behavior: `test_player_dies_at_zero_health`, not `test_works`.
2. Extract pure game logic for unit tests; mock Phaser APIs for scene tests.
3. Reset scene registry, timers, and global stubs between tests.
4. For E2E, drive the game through player-visible flows — not internal scene private fields.
5. When fixing a bug, add a regression test that fails without the fix.
6. Run tests via the project runner (`npm test`, `pnpm test`) — not ad-hoc node invocations.
